  "texts": [
    "The test results for multi-dimensional moral issues reveal the improvement of LLMs' moral competence, as seen through both longitudinal (GPT series) and cross-sectional comparisons (ChatGPT, ERNIE Bot, and ChatGLM).",
    "We then apply Dewey's moral philosophy to explicate the theoretical training process of LLMs and to develop a moral growth model for them (for a detailed discussion of the model, see section \"Discussion\" and Fig. 1).",
    "By comparing the moral learning process of LLMs with those of humans, pre-training data can be seen as analogous to human moral experience, while RLHF serves as a societal evaluative mechanism for orienting their behavior.",
    "The goal of RLHF is to guide LLMs in gradually transitioning from externallyintervened moral learning to self-correction by continuously receiving external moral evaluations, thereby gradually aligning their moral behavior with human values.",
    "However, our experiment results prove that LLMs are not fully capable of recognizing human moral intentions."
  ],
